<sme-documentation name=Break>

<hr>
<h3>Component Semantics:</h3>
<component tag=Break>
  <definition>damage an existing Tangible-Entity so that it can no longer
    serve its function</definition>
  <requiredslot name=object>
    <restriction>a Tangible-Entity</restriction>
    <restriction>must already exist</restriction>
    <restriction>becomes broken</restriction>
  </requiredslot>
  <requiredslot name=post-conditions>
    <restriction><slot>object</slot> is the <slot>object</slot> of a 
      <conceptref name=Be-Broken> <conceptref name=State></restriction>
  </requiredslot>
  <primaryslot name=agent>
    <restriction>causes <slot>object</slot> to Break</restriction>
  </primaryslot>
  <primaryslot name=instrument>
    <restriction>a Tangible-Entity</restriction>
    <restriction>used in Breaking the <slot>object</slot></restriction>
  </primaryslot>
  <primaryslot name=by-means-of>
    <restriction>an Event necessary to the Breaking of the <slot>object</slot></restriction>
  </primaryslot>
  <wnsynsets><verb>break#3, break#17
  </verb></wnsynsets>
  <wnsynsets><verb>break_down#4, conk_out#1, die#4, fail#4, give_out#4, give_way#4, go#30, 
  </verb></wnsynsets>
</component>

<musing>
Strictly, to Break is to cause to <conceptref name=Be-Broken>. The
interpretation is that the <slot>object</slot> is no longer able to
serve its <slot>function</slot>.
</musing>

